The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) in Adamawa, yesterday, announced candidates of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) as winners in the by-election in Nassarawo Binyeri as well as the supplementary election in Uba/Gaya state constituency. The Returning Officer for Uba Gaya State Constituency election, Dr. Adedeji Ahmed of Modibbo Adama University of Technology (MAUTECH), Yola, announced Abbas Aminu Iya of the PDP as winner having scored the highest votes of 7,251 to defeat the runner up, Mohammed Hayatu Atiku of the All Progressives Congress (APC) who scored 7,238 Also, the Returning Officer for Nassarawo Binyeri State Assembly Constituency by-election, Dr Sulaiman Zarma of the Federal College of Education (FCE), Yola, declared the PDP candidate,Â  Umar Nashon Gubi as the winner. Gubi polled 10,733 votes as against his APC counterpart, Mahmud Dabo, who got 7,184. The election was shifted to Saturday following the death of the then incumbent legislator and APC candidate Adamu Kwanate who died two weeks to the general elections. PDP sweeps Nassarawo-Binyreri, Uba/Gaya constituencies in Adamawa APC wins Gabasawa/Doka Constituency in Kaduna North Makarfi, Kudan lose constituencies